==Chinese==
===[[wikipedia:Taiwanese Mandarin|Taiwanese Mandarin]]===
[[Pinyin]]: guīmáo 
===[[Min Nan]]===
[[POJ]]: ku-mo•

===Etymology===
Originally from the Min Nan word ku-mo• (turtle fur).  It was most likely a reference to a Buddhist metaphor that describes hollow logic ([[龜毛兔角]] turtle fur and rabit horns [an impossibility]).

===Adjective===
'''[[龜]][[毛]]'''

# [of someone's personality] [[picky]]; [of someone's personality] [[high maintenance]]; describes somebody with unreasonable expectations

===Alternate forms===
[[龟毛]] ([[Simplified Chinese]])

